gobblin.source.workunit

Class MultiWorkUnit

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.configuration.State
      • gobblin.source.workunit.WorkUnit
        • gobblin.source.workunit.MultiWorkUnit
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable

    public class MultiWorkUnit
extends WorkUnit
    A class that wraps multiple WorkUnits so they can executed within a single task.

    This class also extends the State object and thus it is possible to set and get properties from this class. The setProp(String, Object) method will add the specified key, value pair to this class as well as to every WorkUnit in workUnits. The State.getProp(String) methods will only return properties that have been explicitily set in this class (e.g. it will not retrieve properties from workUnits.
